        "username": "Merrit",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/merrit/{size}/51251_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-03-22T13:10:37.368Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Android <a href=\"https://support.signal.org/hc/en-us/articles/360049670791-Font-Size-Options#android\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">already has</a> the ability to adjust the font size of messages. It would be great if iOS had this as well.</p>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://github.com/signalapp/Signal-iOS/issues/471\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">iOS app already automatically scales</a> based on the user’s system font size preferences, however with this as the only font size option it means I am stuck with my messages being too small for comfort if I already like the font size of the rest of my system.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>As a workaround for the time being, it is possible to set text size with Shortcuts, so it is easy to create an automation to do that when Signal opens/closes.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 6,
        "updated_at": "2025-03-31T18:40:39.670Z",
